{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:05:07.755695+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have all the information needed. Here is the summary:\n\n---\n\n## NPM Scripts in This Repository\n\nThis is a **Create React App template** (`cra-template-firebase-starter`). There are two layers of scripts:\n\n### 1. Root `package.json` (used for developing the template itself)\n\n| Script | Command | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `start` | `react-scripts start` | Start local dev server |\n| `build` | `react-scripts build` | Create production build |\n| `test` | `react-scripts test` | Run tests |\n| `eject` | `react-scripts eject` | Eject from CRA |\n| `predeploy` | `npm run build` | Build before deploy |\n| `deploy` | `gh-pages -d build` | Deploy built app to GitHub Pages |\n| `clean-files` | `rm -rf ./template/public ./template/src` | Clean template directories before publishing |\n| `copy-files` | `cp -a ./src/. template/src && cp -a ./public/. template/public` | Copy current source into the template folder |\n| `prepublishOnly` | `npm run clean-files && npm run copy-files` | Prep template for npm publish |\n\n### 2. `template.json` (scripts that get installed into the user’s project)\n\n| Script | Command | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `start` | `react-scripts start` | Start local dev server |\n| `build` | `react-scripts build` | Create production build |\n| `test` | `react-scripts test` | Run tests |\n| `eject` | `react-scripts eject` | Eject from CRA |\n| `predeploy` | `npm run build` | Build before deploy |\n| `deploy` | `gh-pages -d build` | Deploy to GitHub Pages |\n| `serve` | `serve -s build` | Serve the production build locally |\n| `build-and-serve` | `npm run build && npm run serve` | Build then serve locally |\n| `pull` | `git pull && npm i && npm start` | Pull latest, install deps, start dev |\n\n---\n\n## Guidance for Testing a Production Build Locally\n\n### What the README says (outdated guidance)\